{"parse":{"title":"Wreck (2)/fr","pageid":3035,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><big><big><big>\u00c9pave</big></big></big>\n</p><p>\u00c9pave, \u00e0 la suite d\u2019un sinistre maritime, signifie:\n</p>\n<ol><li>a) un navire coul\u00e9 ou \u00e9chou\u00e9; ou</li>\n<li>b) toute partie d\u2019un navire coul\u00e9 ou \u00e9chou\u00e9, y compris les objets qui se trouvent ou se trouvaient \u00e0 bord d\u2019un tel navire; ou</li>\n<li>c) tout objet perdu en mer, coul\u00e9, \u00e9chou\u00e9 ou \u00e0 la d\u00e9rive, provenant d\u2019un navire; ou</li>\n<li>d) un navire qui est en train, ou raisonnablement susceptible de, couler ou <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"03c7c0ace395d80182db07ae2c30f034\">s</span>\u2019\u00e9chouer, lorsque des mesures efficaces d\u2019assistance au navire ou aux biens en danger n\u2019ont pas encore \u00e9t\u00e9 prises.</li></ol>\n<p><br>\n</p><p>La source: Convention de Nairobi 2017, fourni par le comit\u00e9 <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"47f45e65244c17ec9fa8771a5c6d60e1\">ARM</span> dans le document ARM7-12.1.14 en 2017.\n</p><p><br>\n<i>Ce num\u00e9ro de d\u00e9finition remplace 1-2-205 dans l'\u00e9dition originale du dictionnaire <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> (1970-1989).</i>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Wreck_(2)\" title=\"Wreck (2)\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n\u00a0\u2022\u00a0<span lang=\"fr\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">fran\u00e7ais</a></span>\n\u00a0\u2022\u00a0<span lang=\"es\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Wreck_(2)/es\" title=\"Wreck (2)/es\">espa\u00f1ol</a></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"03c7c0ace395d80182db07ae2c30f034\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>second\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"47f45e65244c17ec9fa8771a5c6d60e1\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Aids to Navigation Requirements and Management Committee (IALA)\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615132027\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.033 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.045 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 76/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1017/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 173/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 3/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   15.928      1 Template:Languages\n100.00%   15.928      1 -total\n 58.65%    9.342      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n-->\n\n<!-- Sav